{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-types-post-js","path":"/2008/07/08/christie-behinde-the-scenes/","result":{"data":{"page":{"title":"Making of Behind the Scenes Video","uri":"/2008/07/08/christie-behinde-the-scenes/","content":"\n<center><div style=\"position:relative;width:100%;display:inline-block;\"><iframe src=\"https://flowplayer.com/e/?t=CHRISTIE%20FILMAKA%20SERIES&#038;%3D&#038;r=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.filmaka.com%2Fchriste-series.php%3Ffilm_id%3D2233\" allowfullscreen style=\"border:none;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;width:100%;height:100%;\"></iframe><div style=\"padding-top:56.25%;\"></div></div></center>\n\n\n\n<p>I filmed, edited, and directed the <a href=\"https://www.filmaka.com/christe-series.php?film_id=2233\">behind the scenes documentary for the Christie (2008) internet comedy video series (7mins)</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>In 2008 my brother entered an online film making competition and I helped out. We did&#8217;t win, but we had a bloody good laugh making comedy videos. And one of our videos did win an award at a Canadian film festival.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>A few days into shooting the Christie (2008) Series we got a phone call from the <a href=\"https://www.filmaka.com/jury.php\">producers at filmaka.com</a> saying they wanted a behind the scenes video. I was working as a production assistant at the time and a Sony Z1 HD camera was thrust into my hands. I shot whenever I could between other duties on set. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>If the series ever gets a cult following, I may release more clips.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>I snatched the main interview at the end of a very busy film shoot. Director Azi Rahman and Actor/Producer/Brother Alec Christie actually had a deadline that day, and Alec can be seen uploading an episode in the background.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2>Also see:</h2>\n\n\n\n<ul><li>You can watch the full Christie series on <a href=\"http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=IKJaoCMzAcc&amp;feature=PlayList&amp;p=8F5EC9D6A8848FD9&amp;index=0&amp;playnext=1\">YouTube</a>, <a href=\"http://www.facebook.com/pages/Christie/15991448677\">facebook</a>, and with additional extras at <a href=\"https://www.filmaka.com/christe-series.php?film_id=2066\">filmaka.com</a><a href=\"http://www.filmaka.com/filmaka_christie.php\">.</a></li><li><a href=\"https://www.filmaka.com/christe-series.php?film_id=2066\">Christie Series Trailer</a> (also <a href=\"/blog/2008/07/08/christie-trailer/\">made by me</a>)</li><li><a href=\"https://www.filmaka.com/search-results.php?searchresults=louie%20christie&amp;searchresults=louie%20christie&amp;film_ids=2264\">American Dream Behind The Scenes video (3 mins)</a></li></ul>\n\n\n\n<p></p>\n","date":"July 8, 2008","excerpt":"<p>I filmed, edited, and directed the behind the scenes documentary for the Christie (2008) internet comedy video series (7mins). In 2008 my brother entered an online film making competition and I helped out. We did&#8217;t win, but we had a bloody good laugh making comedy videos. And one of our videos did win an award [&hellip;]</p>\n","featuredImage":{"node":{"altText":"A camera films in a green screen studio","localFile":{"childImageSharp":{"gatsbyImageData":{"layout":"constrained","backgroundColor":"#68b858","images":{"fallback":{"src":"/blog/static/27729d9623f43b88d4308b75f9e93218/acf90/cropped-christie_ostrich_green_screen-1.jpg","srcSet":"/blog/static/27729d9623f43b88d4308b75f9e93218/159e4/cropped-christie_ostrich_green_screen-1.jpg 190w,\n/blog/static/27729d9623f43b88d4308b75f9e93218/3d3c6/cropped-christie_ostrich_green_screen-1.jpg 380w,\n/blog/static/27729d9623f43b88d4308b75f9e93218/acf90/cropped-christie_ostrich_green_screen-1.jpg 760w","sizes":"(min-width: 760px) 760px, 100vw"},"sources":[{"srcSet":"/blog/static/27729d9623f43b88d4308b75f9e93218/3798e/cropped-christie_ostrich_green_screen-1.webp 190w,\n/blog/static/27729d9623f43b88d4308b75f9e93218/2006b/cropped-christie_ostrich_green_screen-1.webp 380w,\n/blog/static/27729d9623f43b88d4308b75f9e93218/dd6f6/cropped-christie_ostrich_green_sc